sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Procter & Gamble Co. (Symbol: PG), where a total volume of 32,345 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 3.2 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 43.4% of PG's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 7.4 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $85 strike put option expiring June 16, 2017 , with 5,579 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 557,900 underlying shares of PG.

Below is a chart showing PG's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $85 strike highlighted in orange:

Copa Holdings S.A. (Symbol: CPA) saw options trading volume of 1,330 contracts, representing approximately 133,000 underlying shares or approximately 42.8% of CPA's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 310,390 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $95 strike put option expiring November 17, 2017 , with 271 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 27,100 underlying shares of CPA.

Below is a chart showing CPA's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $95 strike highlighted in orange:

And Central Garden & Pet Co (Symbol: CENT) options are showing a volume of 696 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 69,600 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 42.8% of CENT's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 162,490 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $30 strike put option expiring May 19, 2017 , with 505 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 50,500 underlying shares of CENT.
